## Web3 Authentication with Privy (Starter Project)

This is the starter code for the YouTube series Building a Web3 Payment App, where we integrate authentication using Privy into a fullstack application.

In this part of the series, we focus on:

## .Web3 login (frontend)
## .Backend token verification
## .Decrypting and validating user sessions
## .Extracting authenticated user information

## Video Series

This repo is used in:

Building a Web3 Payment App (Fullstack Series)
Episode 1: Web3 Authentication with Privy

## ⚙️ Tech Stack
## .React (Frontend)
## .Node.js / Express (Backend)
## .Privy (Web3 Authentication)
## .JWT-style session handling (via Privy tokens)

## Getting Started
1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/repo-name.git
2. Install dependencies
Backend
cd backend
npm install
Frontend
cd client
npm install
3. Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the backend:

PRIVY_APP_ID=your_privy_app_id
PRIVY_APP_SECRET=your_privy_app_secret
PORT=5000
4. Run the project
Start backend
cd backend
npm run dev
Start frontend
cd client
npm run dev

## What This Project Does
## .User logs in via Privy (wallet or email)
## .Frontend sends auth token to backend
## .Backend verifies token using Privy utilities
## .Server extracts user identity

## Key Learning Outcome

By the end of this part, you will understand:

How Web3 authentication works in real apps
How to verify user sessions on the backend
How to connect frontend auth to backend logic

